#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:145
msgid "Master, these runes seem to hold a protective spell. We may need to break it piece by piece."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:149
msgid "Then we must locate the guardians — no doubt they will appear the moment we set foot on these sigils."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Nagou
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:162
msgid "Nagou"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:169
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:351
msgid "Defeat all enemy units"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:203
msgid "You shall not... enter the sacred sanctum..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:207
msgid "How amusing. Even in death, they cling to hollow oaths. Arkal-Thil, another seal falls."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:240
msgid "<i>With the last guardian vanquished, the runes on the wall fade. The barrier crumbles, revealing a hidden chamber beyond — at its center, surrounded by shallow pools, rests the Book of Crelanu upon a pedestal.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:284
msgid "<i>As Gwiti seizes the tome, tremors shake the cave, and shadows creep from the depths. Feral creatures, bound to the tome’s defense, slink from the pools and shadows.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:310
msgid "Master, the guardians of the cave awaken!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:314
msgid "They are no more than shadows bound by ancient spells. We’ll crush them as we did the keepers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:386
msgid "With the final guardian defeated, a deathly silence settles once more. The tome, now Gwiti’s, pulses with dark power."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:391
msgid "With Crelanu’s knowledge, Wesnoth will witness my wrath. Let us leave this forsaken cave, Arkal-Thil."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:395
msgid "Yes, master. May all who defy you be swallowed by the shadows we leave behind."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:7
msgid "Five years prior... the autumn of the fourth year of King Delvhar I’s reign."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:10
msgid "The northern lands were undergoing a gradual transformation. From among the divided tribes a great chief arose to unite them under a single banner and lead the orcs out of the stagnation that had lasted since the death of Kapou’e, the Son of the Black-Eye."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:13
msgid "Yet the orcs remained true to their nature, pursuing twin ambitions: plunder and conquest."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:17
msgid "They began systematically raiding elven and human settlements and outposts. What struck terror in the hearts of the people was not the familiar pattern of scattered raids, but rather the unprecedented scale of these assaults — massive battles waged by armies of emboldened orcs."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:21
msgid "One such battle took place near the Wesnothians outpost at the Stone of Erzen, where two brother-mages were preparing to perform a ritual that could potentially turn the tide of the war in their favor..."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:30
msgid "But the hopes of humans and necromancers did not come true: the massive orcish reinforcements that arrived later utterly decimated the Wesnothian forces and the remaining undead. The battlefield at the Stone of Erzen turned red with blood and white with bones."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:33
msgid "Consumed by fury, the survivors hunted Gwiti and Nati to bring them to justice. Without the evil interference of the undead, they believed, there would have been no chaos, no defeat no unnecessary deaths. At last, the necromancers were captured."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:36
msgid "The Ha’atel brothers were bound in iron chains and cast aboard a rudderless ship. They were condemned to drown in the endless ocean, for the Wesnothians feared their corpses might rise again from any earthly grave..."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:40
msgid "<i>... but fate had other designs.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:48
msgid "Heeding the enigmatic guidance of a distant voice, Gwiti Ha’atel pressed forward through unfamiliar terrain, drawn inexorably toward a confrontation that seemed to have been orchestrated long before his arrival."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:56
msgid "Once more, the voice of the master resonated in Gwiti’s mind, urging him forward into the depths of his dark destiny."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:59
msgid "<i>“Gwiti, do not be hasty in seeking your vengeance against Wesnoth. The path you tread is fraught with peril, and your ultimate aim requires the Skull of Morgorath. The whispers of the world’s sacrifices beckon you to heed their call.”</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:63
msgid "<i>“Journey forth to the forbidding mountains in the northwest. There, amid the ancient stones, a power awaits that will elevate you beyond your wildest dreams. Embrace this calling, for it shall bestow upon you the strength to shape your fate.”</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:72
msgid "As Gwiti regained his senses, the skies overhead darkened, a thick blanket of clouds rolling in as if in response to his mounting fury. He found himself once again on the desolate battlefield, but this time, the voice that had lured him this far was silent, its influence faded."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:75
msgid "Frustrated and drained from his failed quest, Gwiti looked at the half of the skull in his hand, feeling the weight of wasted time. Half a relic was no path to ultimate power. Still seething, he recalled an artifact from his memory — the Book of Crelanu, a tome of legendary might that had long been sealed away. His resolve hardened; if he could not wield the full Skull, he would claim Crelanu’s tome, bending its power to his own dark designs."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:84
msgid "According to the journal Gwiti uncovered, following the death of Delfador the Great, a custom emerged: the Book of Crelanu would be entrusted only to one of the King’s closest advisors."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:87
msgid "However, this decision proved a grave miscalculation. The tome eventually fell into the hands of Mal-Ravanal, unleashing the deadliest undead incursion Wesnoth had ever faced, nearly bringing the kingdom to ruin."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:90
msgid "In the aftermath, no mage dared claim stewardship of Crelanu’s tome. Instead, the mages resolved to conceal it in a place no mortal would easily reach, while rumors spread that it lay protected within the Tower of Kaleon."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:93
msgid "Now, five centuries later, Gwiti has retraced their steps, descending to the deepest reaches of the underground labyrinth, ever closer to the elusive tome..."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:102
msgid "Concerned about the presence of undead legions within Wesnoth, the king ordered lords across the land to remain vigilant. In the midst of these precautions, one of the elves who had survived the attack on Kaleon’s Tower delivered urgent news to the council Ka’lian."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:105
msgid "Recognizing the gravity of the situation, Lord Caraldur himself led an elven battalion toward the region. Meanwhile, Lord Aretu of Wesnoth and General Leonard mobilized their own forces, converging on the path of Gwiti, as their pursuit brought them all to a single, decisive location."
msgstr ""

